parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants. Additionally, faulty airbag systems can cause unexpected deployments, resulting in injuries or distractions while driving.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly shift into reverse gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage. This issue can also result in loss of vehicle control, especially when the vehicle is on an incline.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into reverse gear unexpectedly
the vehicle rolls backwards when in neutral gear
the gear gets stuck in reverse
the vehicle surges when shifting into neutral or reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pinion inside the differential can cause the rear wheels to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat belt latch can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to latch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to seize or stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident or leaving the driver stranded.
